org.opends.sdk
Interface AttributeValueCollection

All Superinterfaces:
Collection<ByteString>, Iterable<ByteString>
public interface AttributeValueCollection
extends Collection<ByteString>

A collection of attribute values. Some attribute value collections allow duplicate duplicate attribute values and others do not. Some are ordered and others unordered.

Attribute value collection implementations must not permit null attribute values. In addition, implementations must compare attribute values using the equality matching rule associated with the attribute description.

hashCode

int hashCode()
Returns the hash code for this AttributeValueCollection.

Implementations should calculate the hash code by combining the hash code of the attribute description with the hash codes of all the attribute values contained in this AttributeValueCollection. The AttributeValueCollection does not stipulate the hashing algorithm to be used, nor the order in which attribute value hash codes should be combined.

toArray

ByteString[] toArray()
Returns an array containing all of the attribute values contained in this AttributeValueCollection.

If this AttributeValueCollection makes any guarantees as to what order its attribute values are returned by its iterator, this method must return the attribute values in the same order.

The returned array will be "safe" in that no references to it are maintained by this AttributeValueCollection. The caller is thus free to modify the returned array.

Specified by:
toArray in interface Collection<ByteString>

toArray

<T> T[] toArray(T[] array)
            throws ArrayStoreException,
                   NullPointerException
Returns an array containing all of the attribute values in this AttributeValueCollection; the runtime type of the returned array is that of the provided array.

If the set fits in the provided array, it is returned therein. Otherwise, a new array is allocated with the runtime type of the provided array and the size of this AttributeValueCollection. If this AttributeValueCollection fits in the provided array with room to spare (i.e., the array has more elements than this AttributeValueCollection), the elements in the array immediately following the last attribute value are set to null.

If this AttributeValueCollection makes any guarantees as to what order its attribute values are returned by its iterator, this method must return the attribute values in the same order.

Specified by:
toArray in interface Collection<ByteString>
Throws:
ArrayStoreException - If the runtime type of array is not a supertype of ByteString.
NullPointerException - If array was null.

toAttribute

Attribute toAttribute()
Returns the Attribute representation of this AttributeValueCollection. If this AttributeValueCollection is already an Attribute then this method simply returns a reference to this. Otherwise a new Attribute is allocated and all of the attribute values contained in this AttributeValueCollection are added to it using the addAll method.

Returns:
The Attribute representation of this AttributeValueCollection.
